description: A Summer Flounder caught on Long Island's Great South Bay. Also known as Fluke, these flat fish are a popular among recreational fishers in New York. The Fluke fishing season runs from May 4 - September 30th, and Fluke must be at least 19 inches to keep. Always respect the local fishing regulations, and do what you can to limit injury to released fish. Follow on Instagram @wildlife_by_yuri
